properties.name: Conor Lamb
properties.biography: Conor Lamb is the Democratic representative from Pennsylvania's 18th Congressional District in the U.S. House. Lamb won the general special election on March 13, 2018. Lamb won re-election to the U.S. House to represent Pennsylvania's 17th Congressional District on November 6, 2018. He ran in a different district than the one he was elected to represent in the 2018 special election because court-ordered redistricting changed the boundaries of the state's congressional districts.
